<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-01-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="512" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">702.1211 Laredo/54: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Governor of Texas</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moody</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-16">January 16, 1930</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:55
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your wire. Consul General at San Antonio has issued statement that
                            Consulate at Laredo will be opened Friday. I want to express
                            appreciation which I feel and which the citizens of Laredo feel for your
                            efficient assistance in this matter.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dan Moody</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>